juliet m brodie the clayman institute for gender research skip to main content standford university the clayman institute for gender research the clayman institute for gender research home programs news strategic focus events about research fellowships library media center gender news no news found events no events found you are here home people juliet m brodie juliet m brodie professor stanford law school director stanford community law clinic email jmbrodie law stanford edu juilet brodie is a professor at the stanford law school and the director of the stanford community law clinic she received her bachelor's degree from brown university magna cum laude departamental honors 1985 and her jd from harvard law school magna cum laude 1991 her research interests include poverty law and the role of law in advancing economic justice for the have nots in american society professor brodie is a member of the editorial board of the clinical law review and of the executive committee of the section on poverty law at the aals she is co chair 2009 2011 of the aals clinical education section subcommittee on lawyering in the public interest bellow scholar program before joining the stanford law school faculty in 2006 professor brodie was an associate clinical professor at the university of wisconsin law school she was formerly a litigation associate at the boston law firm hill & barlow and assistant attorney general for the state of wisconsin where she prosecuted health care providers accused of defrauding the medicaid system further information about professor juliet brodie is available from her website donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
